Package com.iontrading.mkv

Interface GlobalEventListener

  • @Keep
@KeepPublicClassMemberNames
public interface GlobalEventListener
    Interface for getting notifications for global events like publication, supplies, chain modification, queue supplies, function call/response, transaction call/response.

    • Method Detail

      • onStop

        void onStop()
        Function called to notify that engine is stopping. LogManager is still accessible at this point.

      • onPublish

        void onPublish​(MkvObject object,
               boolean start,
               boolean dwl)
        Function for notifying publication events.
        Parameters:
        object - the MkvObject object representing the publication.
        start - true if the publication is added, false if it is under deletion
        dwl - true if the publication is part of a block of publications (a publish idle event will follow)

      • onUpdate

        void onUpdate​(MkvRecord record,
              MkvSupply supply,
              boolean isSnapshot)
        Event for notifying that an update on the record is received A subscription can fail asynchronously if data entitlements are enabled and the subscriber is not entitled to subscribe a record/pattern; in that case the supply is set to a dummy value and the error code for the MkvRecord is set.
        Parameters:
        record - record object.
        supply - a Supply object representing the changes.
        isSnapshot - true if the current update is a snapshot.
        See Also:
        MkvRecord.getErrorCode()

      • onSupply

        void onSupply​(MkvChain chain,
              String record,
              int pos,
              MkvChainAction action)
        Function called to notify a chain update

        A chain can be modified in a number of ways: inserting or deleting a record, appending a record, changing the content completely (SET) or deleting the content completely (RESET).

        An IDLE event is generated before a chain snapshot which could involve multiple SET events.

        Parameters:
        chain - the MkvChain object.
        record - the record affected by the modification, not significant for SET, RESET, and IDLE actions.
        pos - position of the record affected by the modification, not significant for SET, RESET, and IDLE actions.
        action - the operation done on the chain by the chain publisher.
        See Also:
        MkvChainAction

      • onResult

        void onResult​(MkvTransactionCallEvent event,
              String remote,
              byte code,
              String message)
        Event generated before a response to a transaction request is passed to the caller.

        Generally a code equal to 0 indicates success, other values represent different level of error.

        Parameters:
        event - the associated MkvTransactionCallEvent.
        remote - name of the caller component.
        code - the code returned by the record publisher.
        message - the message string set by the record publisher.
